parts.text:
This document is a "REDACTION CODES" list, outlining 24 categories of information that may be withheld or blacked out from documents released under the Freedom of Information Act 1982. These categories include various types of personal information (e.g., name, address, date of birth, opinions, health, employment history), business information (e.g., bank account details), internal operational information, legal professional communication, deliberative material, irrelevant material, electoral roll data, and material related to law enforcement or compliance procedures.

Its relevance to FOI Request LEX452 is indirect: while not one of the core communications regarding Zi Chun Wang's donations, this document serves as an explanatory key. It indicates the types of information that *could have been redacted* from the actual communications (initial notification, reminder, and acknowledgement of return) released in response to LEX452, ensuring that the recipient understands the basis for any omissions or blackouts in those documents. It clarifies the legal grounds under which certain details might be withheld from the released donor compliance documents.

prompt:
Considering this document as part of an FOI request, summarize the document and its relevance to the FOI request in markdown format. FYI the overview of the FOI request is: FOI Request LEX452 sought documents related to Zi Chun Wang's donations for the 2013/2014 financial year. The released documents, a schedule of three communications from the Australian Electoral Commission (AEC) to Zi Wang, confirm the AEC's process of ensuring compliance with donor disclosure requirements. These communications include an initial notification to Zi Wang regarding his obligation to complete a Donor to Political Party Disclosure Return for 2013/2014, a subsequent reminder, and finally, an acknowledgement from the AEC confirming receipt of his submitted Individual Donor Return for that period, thereby fulfilling his disclosure obligation.
